# Core Flow Integration Report

## What Was Wired

| Component | Before | After |
|---|---|---|
| Wallet address generation | Random fake string in [generateWalletAddress()](file:///d:/Hackathons/Algoplay/algopay/src/server/server.ts#131-141) | Real `intermezzo.createAccount(flowId)` in [server.ts](file:///d:/Hackathons/Algoplay/algopay/src/server/server.ts) |
| GoPlausible registration | [generateBazaarManifest()](file:///d:/Hackathons/Algoplay/algopay/src/monetize/middleware.ts#337-381) not sent anywhere | Live `POST /discovery/resources` in [registerWithBazaar()](file:///d:/Hackathons/Algoplay/algopay/src/x402/bazaar.ts#74-147) |
| CLI command | Missing | `algopay x402 bazaar register <url> --name ... --price ...` |

All changes compile with **0 TypeScript errors** and x402 tests still pass. In **dev mode** (no env vars set), everything falls back gracefully:
- Intermezzo mock → uses `algosdk.generateAccount()` for a real valid address
- Bazaar → returns helpful error message if `BAZAAR_API_KEY` is missing

